What is Amazon Neptune?

Fully managed graph database service in AWS.

Designed for applications that need highly connected data and relationships.

Supports two graph models:

Property Graph (query with Gremlin)

RDF / W3C standard (query with SPARQL)




---

Key Features

Fully managed → AWS handles backups, patching, scaling, and replication.

High performance & low latency → optimized for graph queries.

Highly available → multi-AZ replication with automatic failover.

Secure → VPC, encryption at rest & in transit, IAM integration.

Integration → works with Lambda, SageMaker, QuickSight, and other AWS services.

